Ask HN: Is there a place that specifies input tensors for popular models?
text:
I may be missing something painfully obvious here... but is there any place or way that you can quickly decipher how you create the input tensor from raw data to feed into a model you're working with?

For example, if I grabbed or was given an onnx model, is there any way to discover it's input tensors or is there a central repository of example input tensors I can check?

Every time I find a new pretrained model it semes like a majority of my time is spent just figuring out the input and output tensors and it rarely seems to be properly documented in a reasonable way even on huggingface.

Show HN: Numari – an original number puzzle for Sudoku lovers
text:
Hi HN,

Numari is a number puzzle I've been working on for a few months that I (finally) completed recently. This game was made with the intention of appealing to those who like games similar to Sudoku.

I actually released this as a native app in 2018 (for both iOS and Android), however the rules were a bit too complicated for the initial release (the game used to allow for diagonal movements). Since the general feedback about the game was positive, and since I was looking for an excuse to play with and learn React, I decided to remake the game as a web app with slightly different rules than the original version.

I hope you enjoy it, and I'd very much love to hear your feedback and suggestions!
